{
  "word": "gravity",
  "wordRoot": [
    {
      "title": "<span id=\"#11939\" class=\"scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold flex items-center\"><h1 class=\"inline !mb-1 scroll-m-16 text-3xl font-bold\">gravity</h1><div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\">(n.)</div></span>",
      "html": "<p>约1500年，指\"体重、尊严、严肃、庄重的举止或性格、重要性\"，源自古法语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravité</span>（13世纪）直接源自拉丁语 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravitatem</span>（主格 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravitas</span>）\"重量、沉重、压力\"，源自 <span class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravis</span>\"沉重\"（源自 PIE 词根 <a href=\"/cn/word/*gwere-\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of *gwere-  \" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">*gwere- </a> (1)  \"沉重\"）。科学上指\"由于地球引力而导致地球物体向下加速度\"，首次记录于1620年代。</p><ins class=\"adsbygoogle relative inline-block transition-all inline-block h-[250px] w-[300px]\" data-ad-slot=\"4000736339\" data-adtest=\"off\" data-ad-format=\"auto\" data-full-width-responsive=\"true\"></ins><blockquote class=\"bq-origin\">The words <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravity</i> and <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravitation</i> have been more or less confounded; but the most careful writers use <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravitation</i> for the attracting force, and <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravity</i> for the terrestrial phenomenon of weight or downward acceleration which has for its two components the gravitation and the centrifugal force. [Century Dictionary, 1902]</blockquote><blockquote><i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravity</i> 和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravitation</i> 这两个词有时会混淆使用； 但最仔细的作者使用 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravitation</i> 来表示引力，使用 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gravity</i> 来表示重力或向下加速度的地球现象，它由引力和离心力两个成分组成。[《世纪词典》，1902年]</blockquote>"
    }
  ],
  "relate": [
    {
      "title": "G<div class=\"pl-2 flex-1 text-textSecondary text-xl font-serif\"></div>",
      "html": "<p>罗马人发明的字母表第七个字母； 公元前250年左右引入了改良版的 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">gamma</i>，以恢复“g”音的专用符号。更详细的历史请参见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of C \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/C\">C</a>。</p><p>在元音 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">-e-</i> 、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\">-i-</i> 和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">-y-</i> 之前，古英语的初始 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">g-</i> 发生了变化，现代英语中用辅音 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">y-</i> 来表示（如 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\"><a href=\"/cn/word/year\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of year \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">year</a> </i>、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\"><a href=\"/cn/word/yard\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of yard \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">yard</a> </i>、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\"><a href=\"/cn/word/yellow\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of yellow \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">yellow</a> </i>、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\"><a href=\"/cn/word/young\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of young \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">young</a> </i>、<i class=\"foreign notranslate\"><a href=\"/cn/word/yes\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of yes \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">yes</a> </i>等）。然而，在 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\"><a href=\"/cn/word/get\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of get \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">get</a> </i>和 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\"><a href=\"/cn/word/give\" title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of give \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\">give</a> </i>中，初始的 <i class=\"foreign notranslate\">g-</i> 似乎被斯堪的纳维亚影响所保留。另请参见 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of gu- \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/gu-\">gu-</a>。</p><p>作为美国电影评级的一个等级，于1966年代表 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of general \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/general\">general</a>（adj.）。在物理学中，作为 <a title=\"Etymology, meaning and definition of gravity \" class=\"crossreference notranslate\" href=\"/cn/word/gravity\">gravity</a> 的缩写，最早见于1785年。</p>"
    },
